  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Officer (Electrical Network Project Management)",
  "description": "<p><strong>What You'll Do:</strong></p><p>The selected candidate will be assigned to one of the positions below:</p><p><strong>New Projects</strong></p><ol><li><p>Implement service connection projects for timely power supply.</p></li><li><p>Assist in major works, service connection projects, and HT switching operations.</p></li><li><p>Conduct partial discharge tests on newly commissioned HT cables.</p></li><li><p>Perform site safety audits and liaise with authorities on road opening matters.</p></li><li><p>Monitor project expenditures and update records in the NOVA system.</p></li><li><p>Supervise contractors in electrical installations and miscellaneous works.</p></li><li><p>Handle customer requests, complaints, and issue work orders.</p></li><li><p>Perform standby duty after office hours.</p></li></ol><p><strong>Renewal Projects</strong></p><ol><li><p>Execute distribution cables and equipment renewal projects, including HV works.</p></li><li><p>Plan and implement renewal projects within budget.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with authorities for road opening approvals.</p></li><li><p>Manage manpower and logistics for work activities.</p></li><li><p>Study LV network, perform load transfers, and assist in HV operations.</p></li><li><p>Prepare reports and update project documentation.</p></li><li><p>Supervise contractors, ensure site safety, and address complaints.</p></li><li><p>Perform standby duty after office hours. </p></li></ol><p><strong>What You'll Need:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Diploma in Electrical / Power Engineering or Clean / Renewable Energy or relevant disciplines from any of the recognised Polytechnics in Singapore</p></li><li><p>Relevant working experience would be advantageous</p></li><li><p>Entry level candidates are welcome to apply (On job training will be provided)</p></li><li><p>A team player with good working attitude and basic computer knowledge</p></li><li><p>Possess own transport or driving license would be advantageous but not mandatory</p></li></ol><p><strong>What We'll Provide:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Join us to empower the future of energy</p></li><li><p>There are abundant opportunities to learn, grow and remain relevant in the industry</p></li><li><p>You will have mentorship opportunities with technical experts in various engineering specializations.</p></li></ol>",
